LAGOS – TGN Media Network, publisher of The Gazelle News.com, popular Lagos based online newspaper, is set to celebrate her anniversary and award night. The event with the theme: Advocacy as a Tool for Eradicating Bullying, Cultism, Drug Abuse and Anti-social Vices in Schools is billed for the prestigious D’Podium International Event Centre, Ikeja, Lagos on Thursday, 17 March 2022. Speakers at the event include: Dr. Abari Garba, Director- General, National Orientation Agency (NOA) and Dr. Hamid Bobboyi, Executive Secretary, Universal Basic Education (UBEC). Tinubu Not As Old As Portrayed – Shehu Sani Why Tinubu Is Not Too Old To Contest 2023 Presidency –… Vice President, Prof Yemi Osibajo, GCON, SAN will be the Chairman of the day, Rt. Hon Femi Gbajabiamila, Speaker, House of Representatives will be the Special Guest of Honour while the Chief Host is the Lagos state Governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu. The National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, will also be honoured with Lifetime Achievement Award for his service to Lagos State. Popular Journalist, Babajide Kolade-Otitoju of the Television Continental (TVC) will be honoured with Journalist of the Year award while ‘Journalist Hangout’ is declared the Television Programme of the Year. Expected to compere the event are: Gbenga Adeyinka D 1st and Busola Kukoyi, popular on-air-personality with the Lagos Television.